Traffic Accident Toll Rises to 18 in Turkey
ANKARA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- The death toll of a traffic accident Wednesday night has risen to 18 , the Anatolia News Agency reported Thursday .
An earlier report said that 13 people were killed and at least 15 others injured when a passenger bus collided with an oil tanker in northern Turkey .
The bus hit the tanker in Havza town of Samsun province near the Black Sea , setting the tanker aflame , the report said .
Fire-fighters rushed to the scene and put out the tanker fire , said the agency .
The injured were taken to nearby hospitals for treatment .
An investigation into the cause of the accident is underway .
